msgid ""
"To support the scoping of beans at the `request`, `session`, `application`, "
"and `websocket` levels (web-scoped beans), some minor initial configuration "
"is required before you define your beans. (This initial setup is not "
"required for the standard scopes: `singleton` and `prototype`.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/beans/factory-scopes.adoc:170
msgid ""
"How you accomplish this initial setup depends on your particular Servlet "
"environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/beans/factory-scopes.adoc:174
msgid ""
"If you access scoped beans within Spring Web MVC, in effect, within a "
"request that is processed by the Spring `DispatcherServlet`, no special "
"setup is necessary.  `DispatcherServlet` already exposes all relevant state."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/beans/factory-scopes.adoc:180
msgid ""
"If you use a Servlet web container, with requests processed outside of "
